The paper deals with complexity classes and their relationships, specifically focusing on counting classes such as PP, C_{=}P, and ParityP. This suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves circuit lower bounds, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of immunity and simplicity in the title suggests a connection to logic and set theory, which could place the paper in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the mention of a circuit lower bound derived from Razborov's work suggests a connection to information theory, which could place the paper in cs.IT (Information Theory).
